These questions, categorised based on Read-Heavy and Write-Heavy systems are a must-solve before your next Senior-Level interview at top PBCs like MAANG-M (plus there‚Äôs notes on what each question really evaluates) üëá

üî∏ Read-Heavy Systems
These test your ability to scale while minimizing latency and handling high read loads.

1. Design a URL Shortener (Bitly)
‚Üí Focus: unique ID generation, collision handling, database schema
‚Üí Scale tips: add caching, rate limits, DB sharding

2. Design an Image Hosting Service
‚Üí Focus: object storage (S3/GCS), CDN, image deduplication
‚Üí Add: thumbnail generation, access control, rate limiting

3. Design a Social Media Platform (Twitter/Facebook)
‚Üí Focus: posts, timelines, user relationships (follows/friends)
‚Üí Scale tips: denormalized storage, fanout logic, partitioning strategy

4. Design a NewsFeed System (Advanced)
‚Üí Focus: push vs pull models, ranking logic, user-specific feeds
‚Üí Add: caching layers, pagination, handling spikes in traffic

üî∏ Write-Heavy Systems
These systems test your durability, ingestion speed, real-time processing, and consistency trade-offs

1. Rate Limiter
‚Üí Token Bucket or Leaky Bucket algorithm
‚Üí Redis counters, TTLs, and circuit breakers

2. Log Collection & Analysis System
‚Üí Kafka for ingestion, ELK stack for processing
‚Üí Discuss buffering, partitions, and real-time querying

3. Voting System
‚Üí Handle duplicate votes, ensure idempotency
‚Üí Design for real-time vs eventual aggregation

4. Trending Topics System
‚Üí Count-min sketch for approximations
‚Üí Use sliding window techniques and ranking models




